monstrate how Muslims in different historical contexts responded differently to theological and practical questions. This knowledge will help us better understand the conflicts currently unfolding in parts of the Arab world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aFaith and reasonxIslam. 0aIslamic modernism. 0aIslamic philosophyxHistory. 0aIslamic renewal. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476975440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804769754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804769754.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles